It might not be the best solution to this problem, but my team had the same issue and decided to use two PID settings based on if we are going up or down. We put them in slots 0 and 1 so we could just reference those when adding the setpoint.

public void setPosition(double position) {

if (leftEncoder.getPosition() < position)

controller.setReference(position, SparkBase.ControlType.kPosition, ClosedLoopSlot.kSlot0);

else

controller.setReference(position, SparkBase.ControlType.kPosition, ClosedLoopSlot.kSlot1);

}
